# Environment Variables Template for Vercel

# Copy these variables to your Vercel project settings:
# Settings → Environment Variables

## Required Variables

# Backend API URL (Required)
# The URL where your backend is deployed
# Example: https://cimeika-backend.railway.app
VITE_API_URL=

# Application Name (Optional)
# Display name for the application
# Default: CIMEIKA
VITE_APP_NAME=CIMEIKA

# Participant API Configuration (Optional)
# URL for Hugging Face Participant API
# Default: https://ihorog-cimeika-api.hf.space
VITE_PARTICIPANT_API_URL=https://ihorog-cimeika-api.hf.space

# Participant API Key (Optional)
# Authentication key for participant API
# Leave empty if API doesn't require authentication
VITE_PARTICIPANT_API_KEY=

## Instructions

# 1. Go to your Vercel project dashboard
# 2. Navigate to Settings → Environment Variables
# 3. Add each variable above
# 4. Select environments (Production, Preview, Development)
# 5. Save and redeploy

## Notes

# - All frontend environment variables must start with VITE_
# - Variables are embedded at build time
# - Changing variables requires a new deployment
# - Never commit sensitive data to the repository
